-- 7. Whitstable × Digital Marketing
INSERT INTO public.local_content (service_slug, town_slug, intro_paragraph, local_context, competition_landscape, success_approach, local_stats, pain_points, solutions, faqs, layout_variant)
VALUES (
  'digital-marketing',
  'whitstable',
  'Whitstable''s national reputation as a food and creative destination means the town''s addressable market extends far beyond its 33,000 residents. Weekend visitors from London, food tourists from across the South East, creative buyers discovering Harbour Street online, and an affluent DFL population that engages heavily through digital channels, all represent audiences that digital marketing can reach with precision. Yet most Whitstable businesses market passively, relying on the town''s general reputation to drive footfall without actively reaching the specific audiences most likely to spend. The restaurants that invest in targeted Instagram advertising fill tables on quiet midweek evenings. The galleries that run London-targeted campaigns attract buying visitors rather than just browsers. We build digital marketing campaigns for Whitstable businesses that reach beyond the town''s organic reputation and actively attract the customers who generate the most value.',
  'Whitstable''s digital marketing landscape is rich with channels and audiences. Instagram advertising reaches the foodie and lifestyle audience that Whitstable content naturally attracts. Google Ads captures high-intent searches for dining, accommodation, and activities. Facebook reaches the local and DFL community for service and event promotion. Pinterest drives discovery for the interiors, food, and lifestyle sectors. The Canterbury District context provides geographic targeting options, while the London audience requires demographic and interest-based targeting. Seasonal events create campaign peaks around the Oyster Festival, summer, and the festive period.',
  'Digital marketing among Whitstable businesses is more developed than many Kent towns, particularly in the food sector, but significant gaps remain. Some restaurants and creative businesses run effective Instagram campaigns. Many others rely entirely on organic social posting and the town''s general reputation. Service businesses and trades rarely invest in digital marketing at all. The opportunity exists both to optimise existing marketing efforts and to introduce digital channels to businesses that have not yet explored them.',
  'We build Whitstable digital marketing campaigns around the town''s unique audience composition. Visitor acquisition campaigns target London foodies, lifestyle seekers, and cultural tourists with the specific content they respond to. Local campaigns target the DFL and residential population for service and retail promotion. Seasonal campaigns align with the Oyster Festival, summer peaks, and festive trading. Every campaign tracks to measurable commercial outcomes.',
  '{"population": 33000, "district": "Canterbury", "business_districts": ["Harbour Street", "High Street", "Tankerton", "Harbour area"], "key_fact": "National reputation creates addressable audience far exceeding town population through targeted digital channels"}',
  '[{"title": "Relying on Whitstable''s reputation instead of actively marketing", "description": "Whitstable''s general reputation brings visitors, but not necessarily to your specific business. A foodie visitor drawn by the town''s fame chooses the restaurant that appeared in their Instagram feed last week, not the one they happen to walk past. Active digital marketing determines which businesses capture the visitors the reputation attracts."}, {"title": "Quiet periods unfilled despite available Whitstable audience", "description": "Midweek evenings, off-season weekdays, January and February. These quiet periods cost Whitstable hospitality businesses significant revenue. A targeted Instagram campaign promoting midweek specials to the London foodie audience can fill tables that would otherwise sit empty. Without active marketing, quiet periods stay quiet."}, {"title": "No measurement connecting Whitstable marketing to revenue", "description": "Many Whitstable businesses boost social media posts or run occasional promotions without tracking what actually generates bookings, sales, or visits. Without measurement, marketing budget flows to whatever feels right rather than whatever demonstrably works. Digital marketing with proper attribution solves this."}]',
  '[{"title": "Visitor acquisition campaigns for Whitstable hospitality and retail", "description": "Instagram, Facebook, and Google campaigns targeting the specific London and South East audiences most likely to visit and spend in Whitstable. Foodie demographics, lifestyle seekers, creative buyers. Precise audience targeting puts your business in front of people planning their next coastal visit."}, {"title": "Seasonal campaign management for Whitstable''s trading peaks", "description": "Marketing intensity and messaging aligned with Whitstable''s natural calendar. Oyster Festival campaigns, summer visitor targeting, Christmas shopping promotion, and off-season midweek offers. Budget and creative shift with the seasons to maximise revenue during peaks and sustain it during quieter periods."}, {"title": "Revenue-tracked reporting for Whitstable business decisions", "description": "Monthly reports connecting marketing spend to bookings, sales, and customer acquisition. No vanity metrics. Whitstable business owners see exactly what each campaign and channel produced in measurable business outcomes, with recommendations for ongoing optimisation based on actual performance data."}]',
  '[{"question": "What budget does a Whitstable business need for digital marketing?", "answer": "Instagram advertising targeted at the foodie and visitor audience can start from as little as five hundred pounds monthly and deliver measurable results. Google Ads for high-intent Whitstable searches typically require seven hundred to fifteen hundred pounds for meaningful impact. We always start focused and scale based on proven returns."}, {"question": "Can digital marketing fill quieter midweek periods in Whitstable?", "answer": "Yes. Targeted campaigns promoting midweek offers to the London audience generate bookings for periods that would otherwise be quiet. The foodie demographic is responsive to special offers and experiences, particularly when targeted through Instagram and Facebook with compelling Whitstable visual content."}, {"question": "How do you target London visitors likely to come to Whitstable?", "answer": "We use interest-based targeting combining food and lifestyle interests with London geographic location and demographic profiles matching Whitstable''s typical visitor. Lookalike audiences modelled on your existing customer base extend reach to similar prospects. The targeting becomes increasingly precise as campaign data accumulates."}, {"question": "How quickly will digital marketing generate results for my Whitstable business?", "answer": "Instagram and Facebook campaigns typically generate measurable engagement within the first week and bookings within two to three weeks as campaign optimisation improves. Google Ads can generate enquiries from day one. Most Whitstable clients see positive return on investment within the first month."}]',
  'lead-gen'
)
ON CONFLICT (service_slug, town_slug) DO UPDATE SET
